Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:18 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jeanne Zamzow on 2017CM21 and Atty Justin Sondalle on 2016CM166.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Zamzow - both have offers on each of the cases and may resolve if can talk with the ADA for a few minutes.  Court takes a brief recess.

Court recess at 11:19 a.m.

Court reconvened at 11:35 a.m.  Same appearances.  Atty Zamzow recites agreement - defendant will plea to Count 1 in 2016CM166 and count 1 in 2017 CM21, with probation and count 2 will be dismissed and read-in.  State concurs.  Atty Sondalle concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 as charged in 2016CM166 and on count 1 as charged in 2017CM21 and orders count 2 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by ADA.  Statement by Atty Zamzow.  Statement by Atty Sondalle.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2016CM166 (count 1)

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 1 year concurrent to each other.

CONDITIONS:

-Court Costs.  To be collected be the Clerk of Courts.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
-20 hours of community service.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.
-DNA Sample.

2017CM21 (count 1)

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 1 year concurrent to each other.

CONDITIONS:

-$100 fine plus court costs.  To be collected be the Clerk of Courts.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.

Both counts - Court will allow expungement upon successful completion of probation and payment of fine and court costs.
